  <entry>
    <title>TypeScript 6.0 Released</title>
    <id>urn:uuid:1225c695-cfb8-4ebb-aaaa-80da344efa6a</id>
    <link href="https://releases.example.org/typescript/6.0" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/>
    <link href="https://releases.example.org/typescript/6.0.json" rel="alternate" type="application/json"/>
    <link href="https://releases.example.org/typescript/6.0/comments" rel="replies" type="text/html" count="42"/>
    <updated>2025-03-31T18:30:00Z</updated>
    <published>2025-03-31T10:00:00Z</published>
    <author>
      <name>TypeScript Team</name>
      <uri>https://www.typescriptlang.org</uri>
    </author>
    <category term="typescript" label="TypeScript"/>
    <category term="languages" label="Programming Languages"/>
    <summary type="text">Major release with isolated declarations, decorator metadata, and more.</summary>
    <content type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
        <h2>TypeScript 6.0 Highlights</h2>
        <p>This release brings several <strong>major improvements</strong>:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Isolated declarations for faster builds</li>
          <li>Decorator metadata support</li>
          <li><code>using</code> keyword for resource management</li>
          <li>Improved type narrowing in control flow</li>
        </ul>
        <figure>
          <img src="https://releases.example.org/ts6-benchmark.png" alt="TypeScript 6.0 build benchmarks" width="800" height="400"/>
          <figcaption>Build performance improvements in TS 6.0</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <details>
          <summary>Breaking Changes</summary>
          <ul>
            <li>Minimum Node.js version is now 18.0</li>
            <li>Removed deprecated <code>--out</code> flag</li>
            <li>Strict null checks are now on by default</li>
          </ul>
        </details>
      </div>
    </content>
    <media:group>
      <media:content url="https://releases.example.org/ts6-thumb.png" type="image/png" medium="image" width="320" height="180"/>
      <media:description>TypeScript 6.0 release thumbnail</media:description>
    </media:group>
    <georss:point>37.4220 -122.0841</georss:point>
  </entry>

  <entry>
    <title>Rust 1.85 — Stabilizing async closures</title>
    <id>urn:uuid:2345d786-efab-5678-bbbb-91eb455ffa7b</id>
    <link href="https://releases.example.org/rust/1.85" rel="alternate"/>
    <updated>2025-03-28T14:00:00Z</updated>
    <published>2025-03-28T09:00:00Z</published>
    <author>
      <name>Rust Release Team</name>
      <uri>https://www.rust-lang.org</uri>
    </author>
    <category term="rust"/>
    <category term="systems-programming"/>
    <summary>Async closures, improved borrow checker diagnostics, and new standard library APIs.</summary>
    <content type="xhtml">
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
        <h2>What's New in Rust 1.85</h2>
        <p>The flagship feature of this release is the stabilization of <strong>async closures</strong>:</p>
        <pre><code class="language-rust">let fetch = async |url: &amp;str| -&gt; Result&lt;Response, Error&gt; {
    client.get(url).await
};</code></pre>
        <h3>Standard Library</h3>
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>API</th><th>Status</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>AsyncFn</code></td><td>Stable</td><td>Core async closure trait</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>Vec::extract_if</code></td><td>Stable</td><td>Replaces <code>drain_filter</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>Cell::update</code></td><td>Stable</td><td>In-place cell mutation</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </content>
    <georss:where>
      <gml:Point>
        <gml:pos>47.6062 -122.3321</gml:pos>
      </gml:Point>
    </georss:where>
  </entry>

